{
  "stem": "5388.5",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Approximately.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know whether how big the transport was, but I think about the total taken.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was not only from Vilna, they took from Kaunas too, from Kovne.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I didn't know about it, but we met them later on in Estonia.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was right, it was labor camps, slave labor camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my first thought as we passed, was I thought we go from there to Paneriai, which is six kilometers.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And suddenly the train is moving and moving and moving--",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Absolutely.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was absolutely convinced.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As I told you, when I wrote that note to my father, I was absolutely convinced that's it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Paneriai, that what's I thought only.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But pretty soon, the train left on the Rose Cemetery.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was where Pilsudski's heart was buried, his mother was buried there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And suddenly, I take a look, Dyneburg.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I knew enough of the map that it was Vincent, and now we're in Latvia.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then we arrived in Riga on the railroad station.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we go and run to get water, and I was jumped out, managed to run to the water to bring in to the boxcars.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I saw they were Estonian too because I saw the flag.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH], the blue, black, white on the armbands.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we used to call them the kurats because that's all we heard was kurat, kurat.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we came to Estonia, and they unloaded us in Ereda.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now later on, Ereda became a bigger camp.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It became up to here, but we were still down there in the swamps.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I had boots, nice ones still-- good ones, leather ones-- and we were there in the camp, and we went to work.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Now I went on the road, and I worked on the on the road to [NON-ENGLISH] going through.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
